2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper presents a stochastic, model predictive control algorithm that leverages short-term probabilistic forecasts, which is a common technique in AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses probabilistic forecasts, which can be considered as a machine learning technique. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with autonomous mobility-on-demand systems, which can be considered as a robotics application. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents a control algorithm for dispatching and rebalancing autonomous mobility-on-demand systems.
